Package main

Class Musial

java.lang.Object
main.Musial
public final class Musial
extends java.lang.Object
Main class of MUSIAL (MUlti Sample varIant AnaLysis), a tool to calculate SNV, gene, and whole genome alignments, together with other relevant statistics based on vcf files.
Version:
2.0
Author:
Alexander Seitz, Simon Hackl

    • parseCLArguments

      private static ArgumentsParser parseCLArguments​(java.lang.String[] args)
      Parses command line arguments by instantiating a ArgumentsParser object.

      The command line arguments specified by the user and accepted by the `main` method are passed and used to instantiate an ArgumentsParser object which is returned if all argument validation steps were successful. If any error arises during the parsing step the program exits.

      Parameters:
      args - Arguments parsed from the command line.
      Returns:
      An instance of the ArgumentsParser class.

    • runSnpEff

      private static void runSnpEff​(ArgumentsParser arguments)
      Runs SnpEff (additional annotation of .vcf files)

      The command line arguments specified by the user and accepted by the `main` method are passed to the static method of the SnpEffAnnotator class. The method does not return any value, but all annotated .vcf files generated with SnpEff will be stored in the directory /snpEff/results. If any errors arise during the process the program exits.

      Parameters:
      arguments - Arguments parsed from the command line.

    • preprocessReferenceInput

      private static java.util.HashSet<ReferenceAnalysisEntry> preprocessReferenceInput​(ArgumentsParser arguments)
      Parses the specified reference data and generates a set of analysis entries.

      Each ReferenceAnalysisEntry represents a genomic region of the reference data, for example a single gene, contig, plasmid or full genome. Each such entry contains naming as well as reference sequence information.

      Parameters:
      arguments - Arguments parsed from the command line.
      Returns:
      A HashSet containing ReferenceAnalysisEntry instances specifying genomic regions of the specified reference data that are subject to further analysis.

    • preprocessSampleInput

      private static java.util.concurrent.CopyOnWriteArraySet<SampleAnalysisEntry> preprocessSampleInput​(ArgumentsParser arguments)
      Analyzes the specified sample data and generates a set of analysis entries.

      Each SampleAnalysisEntry represents a sample name and a VCFFileReader instance pointing to the specified input `.vcf` file of the sample.

      Parameters:
      arguments - Arguments parsed from the command line.
      Returns:
      A CopyOnWriteArraySet containing SampleAnalysisEntry instances, each specifying the input for one sample to analyze.

    • invokeSampleAnalyserRunner

      private static VariablePositionsTable invokeSampleAnalyserRunner​(java.util.HashSet<ReferenceAnalysisEntry> analysisEntries, java.util.concurrent.CopyOnWriteArraySet<SampleAnalysisEntry> sampleAnalysisEntries, ArgumentsParser arguments)
      Invokes multi-threaded analysis of the input samples.

      The single steps are implemented in the SampleAnalyser and SampleAnalyserRunnable classes.

      Parameters:
      analysisEntries - A set of ReferenceAnalysisEntry.
      sampleAnalysisEntries - A set of SampleAnalysisEntry.
      arguments - Arguments parsed from the command line.
      Returns:
      A VariablePositionsTable containing the information processed from the specified input.

    • writeOutput

      private static void writeOutput​(ArgumentsParser arguments, VariablePositionsTable variablePositionsTable)
      Generate output files.

      The single steps are implemented in the OutputWriter and IO classes.

      Parameters:
      arguments - Arguments parsed from the command line.
      variablePositionsTable - The VariablePositionsTable containing the information to write output with.
